name: Plasma Refining
description: Refine crude oil with plasma to obtain hydrogen and refined oil.

name: Casimir Crystal (advanced)
description: The utilization of the rare Grating Crystal for the production of Casimir Crystal results in significantly enhanced efficiency.

name: Graphene (advanced)
description: Fire Ice Vein would greatly facilitate the production of graphene.

name: Carbon Nanotube (advanced)
description: It is feasible to produce Carbon Nanotubes using Stalagmite Crystal, however, this ore is quite rare and difficult to locate.

name: Organic Crystal (original)
description: The processing of wood, plant fuel, and water resources yields Organic Crystal.

name: X-ray Cracking
description: Through the catalytic action of hydrogen gas, the refined oil is subjected to X-ray irradiation, leading to its cracking and yielding an increased quantity of hydrogen, as well as a byproduct: Energetic Graphite.

name: Diamond (advanced)
description: Find Kimberlite Ore and you can smelt it to produce diamonds.

name: Crystal Silicon (advanced)
description: The unique fractal structure possessed by Fractal Silicon makes it the preferred material for the efficient production of crystal silicon.

name: Photon Combiner (advanced)
description: The discovery of Grating Crystal would facilitate the production of Photon Combiner.

name: Mass-energy Storage
description: Under the influence of an intense magnetic field, Critical Photons can be converted into Antimatter and hydrogen.

name: Space Warper (advanced)
description: The existence of Gravity Matrix facilitates the production of Space Warpers.

name: Particle Container (advanced)
description: While Unipolar Magnets are exceedingly rare, their discovery would enable more efficient production of Particle Containers.

name: Deuterium Fractionation
description: The successful fractionation of deuterium from liquid hydrogen has greatly advanced the utilization of nuclear fuel.

name: Reformed Refinement
description: By adding hydrogen and coal to refined oil and subjecting it to a process of reformation, a greater quantity of refined oil can be produced.
